✅ Difference between WeakSet and WeakMap (JavaScript)
Both WeakSet and WeakMap store objects weakly, meaning their entries are automatically removed by garbage collection when the objects are no longer referenced.
The key difference is what they store and how they’re used.

🔑 Core Difference (One Line)
	WeakSet stores only objects, while WeakMap stores object–value pairs.

1️⃣ WeakSet
🔹 What it stores
	• ✅ Objects only
	• ❌ No values, just object presence
🔹 Purpose
Used to track objects (yes/no, visited/unvisited, processed/unprocessed).
Example

const weakSet = new WeakSet();
let user = { name: "Raju" };
weakSet.add(user);
console.log(weakSet.has(user)); // true
user = null; // object removed
// Entry disappears automatically
✅ Think of WeakSet as a list of unique objects.

2️⃣ WeakMap
🔹 What it stores
	• ✅ Object keys
	• ✅ Associated values
🔹 Purpose
Used to attach data/metadata to objects without causing memory leaks.
Example

const weakMap = new WeakMap();
let user = { name: "Raju" };
weakMap.set(user, { role: "Admin" });
console.log(weakMap.get(user)); // { role: "Admin" }
user = null; // object removed
// Key + value removed automatically
✅ Think of WeakMap as private storage for objects.

📊 Side‑by‑Side Comparison
Feature	WeakSet	WeakMap
Stores	Objects only	Object → value pairs
Keys allowed	Objects	Objects
Values stored	❌ No	✅ Yes
Garbage collected	✅ Yes	✅ Yes
Iterable	❌ No	❌ No
Size property	❌ No	❌ No
Primary use	Object tracking	Object metadata

🧠 Memory Diagrams
WeakSet
Object ──▶ WeakSet
   ↑
(no other references)
→ GC removes object
→ WeakSet cleans entry

WeakMap
Object ──▶ WeakMap ──▶ Value
   ↑
(no other references)
→ GC removes object
→ Key & value removed


✅ When to Use Which?
Use WeakSet when:
✔ You only need to know whether an object exists
✔ Tracking processed / visited objects
✔ Preventing duplicate processing
Example:
	• “Has this DOM element already been handled?”

Use WeakMap when:
✔ You need to associate data with an object
✔ Implementing private fields
✔ Attaching metadata safely
Example:
	• “Store user permissions without exposing them”

🎯 Interview One‑Liners
	• WeakSet:
“A collection of objects stored weakly, used for tracking object presence.”
	• WeakMap:
“A key–value store where object keys are garbage‑collected automatically.”

💡 Quick Rule to Remember
	No values → WeakSet
	Key + value → WeakMap

